description: Includes part one of the three part Way of the Wookie, the first story produced specifically for the UK Star Wars title, as its weekly schedule meant it was temporarily running out of material to reprint from the monthly US Star Wars title. The entire story was later reprinted in Marvel Illustrated Books Star Wars 1.
Includes Chewbacca Fights Alone!, the second part of Way of the Wookie!, a story produced specifically for the UK Star Wars Weekly.
Includes Switch, the third and final part of Way of the Wookie!, the first Star Wars story produced especially for the UK Star Wars Weekly.

description: Collected from G.I. COMBAT #138 and OUR FIGHTING FORCES #123- 150, Captain Johnny Cloud, Captain Storm, Gunner Mackey and Sarge Clay – team up as The Losers. Even though these heroes always won in the end, they had to do everything the hard way!

description: When Penguin's assassin fails to kill Joker, the bird is looking for someone to finish the job. Deadshot is ready to fill that position...if he can meet Penguin's (murderously) high standards!
name: Operation: Kill Joker (Part 1)

description: Monthly series reprinting Now's Slimer! With free gift poster.
name: Slimer! 1

description: Collected Comics reprinted full stories from The Real Ghostbusters weekly comic.
name: Collected Comics 1

description: The Daemonites have taken everything from Cole Cash, and now the world's greatest con artist will find himself the victim of an absolutely alien grift, forcing him to make a choice: die at their blue hands, or kill his own brother. Cole will fight his way to his own finish line in the streets of Paris, amid the fires of burning alien bodies.
name: ...Must Come Down

description: Spinning directly out of the hit video game BATMAN: ARKHAM CITY, this new series explores the world behind the game in stories focusing on both heroes and villains and how they came to their roles in ARKHAM CITY. A prequel to the game created with the developer, Rocksteady, this first issue features content previously available only as a digital release and explores the Catwoman/Two-Face rivalry and how it leads them into the clutches of Hugo Strange.
name: Inside Job

description: COBRA COMMAND AFTERMATH! Devastated by the events in COBRA COMMAND, the team reflects on the life and death of fan-favorite character, CHUCKLES. Meanwhile, the survivors of COBRA COMMAND make peace with horrors of the past… and prepare the horrors of the future.
name: The Last Laugh; Cobra Command Aftermath

description: ENTER THE WORLD OF MAGIC! With just his slight-of hand skills, stage magician Terry Ward finds himself in a world he didn’t make—a world where sorcery is real! When he befriends a kid from this world, will danger come calling? You bet it will!
name: Cut and Restore

description: Cry havoc, and let slip the hounds of hell. Malateste and his hunters are in full cry as they pursue Travis through the labyrinth of Lord Baal’s tower. Travis’ goal is to find the lost memories of Jacomo Terence and take them back, but the only way to do it is to surrender his own identity forever. And one step away, in the strange otherworld known as the Mirrortime, Lord Baal is waiting to ensnare him into a bizarre confrontation.

description:
The mind-bending terror of the Elder Gods has infested countless universes. Reality, and humanity itself, hang in the balance. Now it all comes down the final battle. C.V.O. is scattered across America, and one of their own may be the key to stoping the threat once and for all—but not without a tremendous sacrifice. Danger Girl and others are on hand to help, but will it be enough?

General Notes

Bumblebee, Raphael and Snake-Eyes appear only on cover.
